The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                            Business Briefs
                              
	 Berlin, Feb. 10: Tata Motors will create a European version of the Nano within four years, a company executive said. In four years, were going to develop a successor (to the bargain-rate Nano car) that will respect Euro-5 rules on exhaust emissions and European requirements in terms of safety standards, Girish Wagh, head of Tata Motors small vehicles department, said. Wagh did not say how much the European spin-off might cost.                             
	 New Delhi, Feb. 10: The Rangarajan Committee, which is considering relief for the rupee-hit exporters, is likely to submit its report to the Prime Ministers Office this week, suggesting benefits that may be announced in the budget.                            
	 New Delhi, Feb. 10: The Hinduja group is expanding its global automotive business with plans to widen the product portfolio of its commercial vehicles and foundries by making forays into components, construction equipment and technology.                            
	 New Delhi, Feb. 10: Industry body Assocham has suggested Russia and India should draw a joint action plan along with China and Brazil to avert an economic slowdown, which can be triggered by the financial crisis in the US.                            
	 New Delhi, Feb. 10: The government may allow foreign direct investment for specific sectors such as electronic and sports goods in retail if an expert study on the issue sees no impact on small stores, commerce minister Kamal Nath said.                                                                                                                           
